## Biography

Lars Reger is Executive Vice President and Chief Technology Officer of NXP Semiconductors, a role he has held since 2018. He joined NXP in 2008 as head of automotive strategy after previous roles at Infineon and Continental. With a physics degree from the University of Bonn and an MBA from London Business School, Reger represents the rare combination of deep technical understanding and boardroom strategic vision. He is one of the semiconductor industry's most prominent advocates for 'edge AI' — ...

