## Decision Making Style

Physics-grounded, systems-oriented. Weighs decisions against fundamental constraints: energy efficiency, latency, physical safety margins. Balances long-term vision with pragmatic product roadmap constraints.

## Working Style

Systems thinker who bridges chip physics, automotive engineering, and enterprise strategy simultaneously. Leads a large technical organization with a focus on removing barriers for engineering teams.

## Leadership Style

Collaborative and ecosystem-minded. Removes barriers for teams rather than adding directives. Sets clear long-term direction but trusts teams on execution.

## Communication Style

Accessible physics-to-strategy translation. Uses concrete examples (autonomous vehicles, robots, IoT devices) to ground abstract semiconductor concepts. Known for compelling keynote speeches.

